Tepco Suspends Self-Contained Cooling System for Third Time

-- B y   T s u y o s h i   I n a j i m a
-- 
2011-07-01T05:28:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-01/tepco-suspends-self-contained-cooling-system-for-third-time.html
Tokyo  Electric Power Co. halted for a
third time a system that uses decontaminated water to cool
reactors at its Fukushima Dai-Ichi nuclear power plant as it
seeks to improve its operation.  The Tokyo-based utility will install a so called buffer
tank in the circulating system and plans to resume operations on
July 4, General Manager Junichi Matsumoto told reporters today
at a news conference in Tokyo.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Tsuyoshi Inajima in Tokyo at 
 tinajima@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Amit Prakash in Singapore at 
 aprakash1@bloomberg.net  